@pfeatherstone any kind of preloading of weights is possible, but this is custom work you'll have to program on your own, by definition. 

The default repo first creates a randomly intialized model according to your `--cfg`. Then it attempts to transfer any `--weights` specified into the model. This is a layer by layer operation: if a layer has the same name and if it fits, it's transferred, if not that layer is left with it's random initializations.

https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/579fdc57f89e1760e519e0d45e13195bd302e551/train.py#L111-L117
